  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to test the feasibility of using thermal images to diagnose
      bacterial pneumonia instead of a chest x-ray in the future. More specifically, the objectives
      of this study are: 1) to determine if thermal imaging, using a commercial thermal camera can
      detect areas of heat emitted from the chest in similar locations to where a chest X-ray shows
      focal consolidation consistent with bacterial pneumonia; 2) to evaluate whether changes in
      heat emitted from the chest changes over time if it is possible to obtain serial images of
      the chest.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
